## Project Overview

This project simulates a complete data analytics workflow for **NayePankh Foundation**, a non-profit organisation running eight social impact programmes across India. The pipeline:

- Generates realistic synthetic datasets (500 beneficiaries, 300 donations, 200 volunteers)
- Computes KPIs and trend analyses
- Produces four interactive Plotly dashboards
- Runs RFM donor segmentation and programme impact scoring
- Forecasts FY 2025–26 metrics using linear regression
- Audits data quality across all three datasets
- Outputs a single self-contained HTML report with a sticky navigation menu

No external database or API is required — the entire pipeline runs locally.

---

## Features

| Feature | Description |
|---|---|
| **Sticky Navigation Menu** | 12-section sidebar with active-link highlighting as you scroll |
| **Executive Summary** | Auto-generated narrative paragraph using live KPI values |
| **KPI Dashboard** | 12 key performance indicators rendered as metric cards |
| **Overview Dashboard** | 6-panel Plotly subplot (programmes, sources, trends, age, category, completion) |
| **Month-over-Month Table** | Monthly donations and beneficiary counts with ▲/▼ change badges |
| **Programme Analysis** | Satisfaction scores and state-wise beneficiary distribution |
| **Impact Score Calculator** | Weighted composite score (0–100) per programme across 5 dimensions |
| **Donation Analytics** | Quarterly totals and source breakdown charts |
| **Donor RFM Segmentation** | Recency × Frequency × Monetary scoring into 5 donor segments |
| **Volunteer Analytics** | Year-on-year growth and skill distribution |
| **Predictive Analytics** | Linear trend forecast for all 12 months of FY 2025–26 |
| **Data Quality Report** | Null counts, completeness scores, and type checks per column |
| **Enhanced Footer** | Timestamp, dataset sizes, analysis period, confidentiality notice |

